            <p>Montreal 13 Octr 5627.<lb/>
                The Rev S. Morais<lb/>
                Philadelphia<lb/>
                My dear sir.<lb/></p>
            <p>Mr Maurice Kaplan&#91;&#63;&#93;<lb/> the bearer of this&#44; is a gentleman of<lb/> great erudition and of varied<lb/> attainments and is well deserving<lb/> all the attention of our brethren in<lb/> the U. S.  He is a son of &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/> of Minsk who was author of &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/> an excellent book&#44; of which I possess<lb/> a copy.  Mr Kaplan is a Spanish<lb/> scholar&#44; and desires to publish a<lb/> book of which I think very favorably.<lb/>  He will no doubt show it you.  Should<lb/> you be able to forward his views<lb/> you would greatly oblige<lb/></p> 
            <p>Yours ever faithfully<lb/>
                						Abraham de Sola<lb/></p>
            <p>kind remembrance of<lb/>
                self &#38; Mrs DeS. to Mrs Morais<lb/></p>
            
        </body>
    </text>
